case 1) simple addition operation with 2 hardcoded values
case 2) simple arithmetic operation with 2 hardcoded values
case 3) simple arithmetic operation with 2 dynamic values passing at execution of the script ("sh art3.sh 10 5")
case 4) simple arithmetic operation with 2 dynamic values prompting at execution of the script sh arith4.sh

Case 5) -eq -ne -lt -gt -le -ge


Asks for two numbers.

Prints their sum, difference, product, quotient, and remainder.

#!/bin/bash

echo "enter value of a :" a
read a
echo "enter value of b :" b
read b
echo
echo A=$a B=$b
echo "==========="
echo "Sum of two numbers $(( a + b ))"
echo "difference of two numbers $(( a - b ))"
echo "product of two numbers $(( a * b ))"
echo "divison of two numbers $(( a / b ))"
echo "modulus of two numbers $(( a % b ))"



#!/bin/bash
a=$1
b=$2
echo A=$a B=$b
echo "Sum of two numbers $(( a + b ))"
echo "difference of two numbers $(( a - b ))"
echo "product of two numbers $(( a * b ))"
echo "divison of two numbers $(( a / b ))"
echo "modulus of two numbers $(( a % b ))"

